In this painting, Saville depicts a reclining nude figure with female breasts and genitalia, but with a masculine, bearded face.
The genitalia is thrust to the foreground, making it much more of a focus in the picture than the gaze.
The arms and legs of the figure are only partly seen, the extremities lying outside the boundary of the picture.
